The TOI-892 Exoplanetary System


Overview

TOI-892 is a star with 1.28 times the mass of the Sun, and 1.39 times its radius. It is located 1110.70 light years away from the solar system and is estimated to be 2.2 billion years old, as compared to the Sun which is roughly 4.6 billion years old.

TOI-892 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the TOI-892 system


TOI-892 b

TOI-892 b was discovered by the Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS) observatory, in 2020-11, using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.09 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of TOI-892 b is 302.100 times the mass of Earth. The radius of TOI-892 b is 11.994 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, TOI-892 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
